1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 49-04.1 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the installation of smart meters; and to amend and reenact section
3 49-04.1-01 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to unauthorized metering.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 49-04.1-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 49-04.1-01. Definitions.
8 As used in this chapter, unless the context or subject matter otherwise requires:
9 1. "Bypassing" means the act of attaching, connecting, or in any manner affixing any
10 wire, cord, socket, motor or other instrument, device, or contrivance to the utility
11 supply system or any part thereof in a manner as to transmit, supply, or use any utility
12 service without passing through an authorized meter for measuring or registering the
13 amount of utility service.
14 2. "Customer" means the person responsible for payment for utility services for the
15 premises and includes employees and agents of the customer.
16 3. "Smart meter gateway device" means any electronic device producing an electronic
17 signal extending outside the device, which serves as an electric utility load control
18 device, and which is a device ancillary to the electric utility meter located at the end
19 user's residence or business, and the device either:
20 a. Serves as a communications gateway or portal to appliances, equipment, or
21 devices using electricity, water, or gas in the end user's residence or business; or
22 b. Otherwise communicates with appliances, equipment, or devices using electricity,
23 water, or gas in the end user's residence or business.
