1 4. "Tampering" means damaging, altering, adjusting, or in any manner interfering with or
2 obstructing the action or operation of any meter provided for measuring or registering
3 the amount of utility service passing through the meter.
4 4.5. "Unauthorized metering" means removing, moving, installing, connecting,
5 reconnecting, or disconnecting any meter or metering device for utility service by a
6 person other than an authorized employee or agent of a utility.
7 5.6. "Utility" means any public utility, municipally owned utility, or cooperative utility which
8 provides electricity, gas, or water, or any combination thereof, for sale to consumers.
9 6.7. "Utility service" means the provision of electricity, gas, water, or any other service or
10 commodity furnished by the utility for compensation.
11 7.8. "Utility supply system" includes all wires, conduits, pipes, cords, sockets, motors,
12 meters, instruments, and all other devices used by the utility for the purpose of
13 providing utility service.
14 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 49-04.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
15 and enacted as follows:
16 Installation of smart meter gateway device - Consent required - Required disclosures .
17 1. A utility service may not install a smart meter gateway device on or in a person's home
18 or business without providing a form as prescribed under this section which must be
19 signed by the property owner. The form must contain the following statement in at
20 least twelve - point type :
21 a. You may op t - out of the installation of a smart meter gateway device ;
22 b. If you choose to op t - out of the installation, service provided by this utility service
23 will not be interrupted or hindered; and
24 c. For your information, a smart meter gateway device is any electronic device
25 producing an electronic signal extending outside the device, which serves as an
26 electric utility load control device, and which is a device ancillary to the electric
27 utility meter located at the end user's residence or business, and the device
28 either:
29 (1) Serves as a communications gateway or portal to appliances, equipment, or
30 devices using electricity, water, or gas in the end user's residence or
31 business; or
