2 electricity, water, or gas in the end user's residence or business.
3 2. Upon first providing services to a person's residence or business, the utility service
4 shall disclose in writing whether a smart meter gateway device has been installed, and
5 if installed, the utility service shall allow the removal of a smart meter gateway device
6 upon written request from the owner of the residence or business. Upon removal, a
7 traditional legacy electromechanical meter must be installed in place of the smart
8 meter gateway device.
